#: ../../../system/riscv/mips.rst:2
msgid "Boards for RISC-V Processors by MIPS"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../system/riscv/mips.rst:4
msgid ""
"RISC-V processors developed by MIPS support Boston-aia board model. The "
"board model supports up to 64 harts with MIPS CPS, MIPS GCR, MIPS CPC, AIA "
"plic, and AIA clint devices. The model can create boot code, if there is no "
"```-bios``` parameter. Also, we can specify ```-smp x,cores=y,thread=z```."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../system/riscv/mips.rst:10
msgid "Running Linux kernel"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../system/riscv/mips.rst:12
msgid ""
"For example, to use 4 cores and 2 threads with each core to have 8 smp cpus, "
"that runs on the ```mips-p8700``` CPU, run qemu as follows:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../system/riscv/mips.rst:15
msgid ""
"qemu-system-riscv64 -cpu mips-p8700 \\\n"
"      -m 2G -M boston-aia \\\n"
"      -smp 8,cores=4,threads=2 -kernel fw_payload.bin \\\n"
"      -drive file=rootfs.ext2,format=raw -serial stdio"
msgstr ""
